{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5d602a25-b046-49a8-8326-54bbd9c920fd","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update both base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet --version` to confirm the SDK, then `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` to verify everything compiles. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any breaking changes in APIs you use.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0b05b1a0-e816-4beb-a390-233d29d0013c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question - I don't need to search any files since they've described their setup. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":296,"requestId":"B829:2234D2:1891762:1B8B4E5:69FD400C"},"id":"54d357fc-3565-4c16-a4f5-c485a8d7a89f","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:44:50.326Z","parentId":"91991b90-02e4-46b3-a2b3-965a937a02c5"}
